{
  "stem": "1550.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] We really were able to clean ourselves again after being on that ship for about two months or whatever, right?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We arrived-- by the way, we arrived in-- in Haifa-- let me see-- we arrived in Haifa on November the 24th.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we had left Tulcea-- we had left Tulcea on October the 7th of 1940, and we arrived in Haifa on November the 24th.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's the period we were on that-- on that-- on the terrible ship, on the Atlantic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a long time, you know, in those conditions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were in this camp, and we were quite happy there because we figured, you know, OK, we'll stay in the camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe we'll stay another two months or whatever, and then we'll be discharged.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Great.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But that was not to be.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The British, for one reason or the other-- political or whatever-- they were fighting alone.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You remember France was defeated?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They probably didn't want to have any problems with the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There are 3,500 people come that are illegal, and they-- you know, the political troubles.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- they said, well, all these people are going to be deported.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, all these people who had already been on the-- on the Patria, they also were supposed to be deported.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then, because there was this terrible accident, or this-- the Patria capsized, the British government modified their decision.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They said as follows-- those people who had been on the Patria and who had been saved-- 250 died, by the way. 250 drowned.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there were about-- about 1,500 or 1,700 people on the Patria, plus the crew and police and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Those people who had been-- those refugees who had been on the Patria, they could stay in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
